  "prompt": "How can one write an essay after reading?",
  "response": "Here are steps to write an essay after reading:\n\n1. Analyze the text\n- Identify main ideas\n- Note key arguments\n- Understand author's perspective\n- Highlight important quotes\n\n2. Develop a thesis statement\n- Create a clear, concise argument\n- Base it on your interpretation of the text\n- Make it specific and debatable\n\n3. Outline your essay\n- Introduction paragraph\n- Body paragraphs\n- Conclusion\n- Allocate main points to each section\n\n4. Write the introduction\n- Provide context about the text\n- Include thesis statement\n- Briefly mention key points\n\n5. Craft body paragraphs\n- Start with topic sentences\n- Use evidence from the text\n- Analyze and explain quotes\n- Connect ideas to thesis\n- Use proper transitions\n\n6. Write the conclusion\n- Restate thesis\n- Summarize main points\n- Provide final insights\n- Avoid introducing new information\n\n7. Edit and proofread\n- Check grammar and spelling\n- Ensure logical flow\n- Verify citation format\n- Read aloud for clarity\n\n8. Optional: Include citations\n- Use appropriate academic style (MLA, APA)\n- Cite direct quotes\n- Reference source material",
